#                   initialization + (optional) weval AOT compilation
#                   (TypeScript/JavaScript, 373★)
#
# upstream: https://github.com/bytecodealliance/ComponentizeJS
# author : Bytecode Alliance (the WebAssembly standards body that
#          maintains wasmtime, jco, wasm-tools, wit-bindgen, wasi-libc,
#          and most of the official Wasm tooling)
# license: Apache-2.0
# npm    : `@bytecodealliance/componentize-js` (provides single
#          `componentize-js` bin via src/cli.js)
#
# Source-direct completion: every flag below is verbatim from src/cli.js
# on the bytecodealliance/ComponentizeJS tip — the `commander` (TJ
# Holowaychuk's commander.js) `.option(...)` / `.requiredOption(...)`
# /  `.addOption(new Option(...).choices(...))` registrations parsed
# exactly as declared, with `--disable` populated from the exported
# `DEFAULT_FEATURES` array in src/componentize.js (stdio / random /
# clocks / http / fetch-event).
#
# Direct deps from package.json (selected):
#   @bytecodealliance/jco              ^1.15.1  ← canonical JS-side
#                                                 WebAssembly Component
#                                                 toolchain (this axis)
#                                                 — by Bytecode Alliance
#                                                 (bytecodealliance/jco);
#                                                 the JavaScript
#                                                 Component Tools that
#                                                 wrap wasmtime
#                                                 internals for JS
#                                                 consumers: transpile
#                                                 a Wasm Component to
#                                                 ECMAScript modules,
#                                                 generate TypeScript
#                                                 type bindings from a
#                                                 .wit file, parse and
#                                                 print component
#                                                 metadata, and run
#                                                 the component
#                                                 directly via a Node/
#                                                 browser embedding of
#                                                 the preview2 shim.
#                                                 jco is to JS what
#                                                 wasmtime is to Rust
#                                                 (host runtime +
#                                                 toolchain) and what
#                                                 wazero is to Go.
#   @bytecodealliance/wizer            ^10.0.0  (Wizer — pre-initialize
#                                                 a Wasm module by
#                                                 running it once and
#                                                 snapshotting the
#                                                 resulting linear
#                                                 memory + globals as
#                                                 the new starting
#                                                 state.  For
#                                                 SpiderMonkey-on-Wasm,
#                                                 this means the JS
#                                                 parser/lexer/runtime
#                                                 init runs ONCE at
#                                                 build time, so
#                                                 startup latency at
#                                                 runtime is ~0.)
#   @bytecodealliance/weval            ^0.4.1   (weval — Wasm Eval,
#                                                 ahead-of-time
#                                                 compiles JS into
#                                                 native Wasm by
#                                                 specializing the
#                                                 SpiderMonkey
#                                                 interpreter against
#                                                 the user's JS at
#                                                 build time.  This is
#                                                 the --aot flag.
#                                                 Trades build time for
#                                                 runtime perf — orders
#                                                 of magnitude faster
#                                                 startup and steady-
#                                                 state throughput.)
#   @bytecodealliance/preview2-shim    ^0.17.4  (Pure-JS implementation
#                                                 of the WASI preview2
#                                                 host interface — so
#                                                 components produced
#                                                 by componentize-js
#                                                 can run in Node /
#                                                 browser environments
#                                                 without a native Wasm
#                                                 runtime in the loop.)
#   commander                                   (TJ Holowaychuk's CLI
#                                                 parser — .option /
#                                                 .requiredOption /
#                                                 .addOption(new Option
#                                                 ()).choices() API)
#
# componentize-js takes a normal ECMAScript Module file (`my-impl.js`)
# implementing the exports declared by a WIT (WebAssembly Interface
# Types) world file (`my-world.wit`), embeds it inside a SpiderMonkey
# JavaScript engine compiled to Wasm, optionally pre-initializes the
# engine state via Wizer, and emits a single .wasm Component that any
# host (wasmtime, wazero, jco, browser) can run.  This is the canonical
# path for "I have an existing JS library and want to ship it as a
# language-agnostic Wasm Component" — the produced component can be
# called from Rust / Go / Python / .NET / any language with a WIT
# binding generator.  With --aot, weval specializes SpiderMonkey
# against your specific JS at build time, eliminating most of the
# interpreter overhead at the cost of a longer build (and a larger
# output).
#
